    • ParkingSlot

      public ParkingSlot(String slotId, boolean isStaffSlot)
      Constructs a new ParkingSlot with the given slot ID and type.
      Parameters:
      slotId - the unique ID of the slot (format: one uppercase letter followed by two digits, e.g., "F01")
      isStaffSlot - true if the slot is for staff, false if it is for visitors
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the slot ID does not match the required format

    • parkCar

      public boolean parkCar(Car car)
      Attempts to park a car in this slot. A car can only be parked if the slot is unoccupied and the car type (staff or visitor) matches the slot type. When parked, the current time is recorded in the Car object.
      Parameters:
      car - the Car to park
      Returns:
      true if the car was successfully parked, false if not

    • removeCar

      public boolean removeCar()
      Removes the car from this slot, if one is parked.
      Returns:
      true if a car was successfully removed, false if the slot was already empty
